article.headline: Rutgers 79, Seton Hall 45
article.story:
HARTFORD, Conn. -- Brittany Ray scored 17 points and Rutgers routed Seton Hall 79-45 Saturday in the second round of the Big East tournament.

Khadijah Rushdon and Epiphanny Prince each added 15 for the Scarlet Knights (19-11), who will face seventh-ranked Louisville in the quarterfinals Sunday. Prince moved into 10th place on the school's all-time scoring list with 1,459 points for her career.

Noteisha Womack scored 12 points and Ebonie Williams added 10 for Seton Hall (17-14), which is hoping its first-round upset of Georgetown will be enough to earn it a WNIT bid.

This one was over early. Rutgers jumped out to a 12-2 lead and then held Seton Hall without a field goal for over five minutes. Midway through the first half it was 22-5. It was 44-20 at intermission.

Rutgers has never failed to make the quarterfinals of the Big East tournament.
